People like to overcomplicate their grilled cheese sandwiches.
All these fancy sourdough rye baguette focaccia brioche whatsits and whatnots.
Me, I like it simple. White bread from Wonder Bread.
Economical and delicious, everything you need in a slice of bread.
It’s just so soft and pillowy, it really takes me back to when I was a kid watching Saturday morning cartoons.
Mom would grill up a sandwich for me if I promised to clean my room.
I always cleaned my room, by the way.
A lot of people just spread butter all over their bread but I can tell you’re not one of those people.
Little trick that mom picked up from one of her chef-y friends was to spread mayo instead of butter on the exterior faces of the bread.
Gives the sandwich that amazing color and crispness when it gets grilled up. It also adds a little overall tang, which is nice when you’re eating a metric ton of cheese.
To this day, I still swear by swapping out the butter for mayo.
Although I won’t complain either way. A grilled cheese is a grilled cheese. You can’t mess it up.
How did you figure out my all-time favourite Special Cheese Combo Mix™?
3 slices of all-American processed cheese, fresh out of their little plastic packets.
You put one slice on each piece of bread. But wait, you say, there’s one more slice? Heh.
You tear up that last slice into strips to cover all the empty spaces of bread left.
If I was extra good that week, mom would even let me have a fourth slice.
This isn’t traditional by any means but I love sprinkling a few sundried tomatoes over the cheese.
It’s not something that mom used to do, I just really appreciate the little bursts of concentrated tomato amidst all the gooey cheesiness.
It took quite some convincing but mom finally conceded to trying it out when I got older.
This was long after all the Saturday-morning shows turned into Saturday-morning gaming sessions with the boys.
I can’t remember the last time I picked up a controller. I wonder if the guys are doing alright. I hope they’re doing better than I am.
Back in school we used to get made fun of for playing our military simulator games. They’d call us nerds and other words I’d rather not mention.
And then I signed up for the army.
Nothing really beats a good ol’ grilled cheese sandwich on rainy days. Days when you want to curl up in bed and forget all the shit you feel.
Things used to be so simple when I was a kid. When mom was alive. I miss her.
This sandwich really takes me back to those simpler times.. That’s comfort food, right?
